variables:

    - Variables are meant for storing the data
    - we can store all categories of data by using variables
    ex: Primitive data , customised data
    - Variables we can declare by using "var" keyword

    Ex.

        //storing the string.
        var var_one = "AngularJS";

        //storing the integer.
        var var_one = 10;

        //storing the objects
        var var_one = new Date();

        //storing the json objects.
        var var_one = {'sub_one':'AngularJS'};

    - In general we can display the data (print) in following ways.

    1. display the data on console(browser console).

    console.log(var_one);

    2. display the data on web page.

    document.write(var_one);

    - we can use <script></script> tag to embed the javascript to web pages.

    Syntax.

        <script type="text/javascript">

            //Business Logic

        </script>



- in javascript local scope changes effecting the global change , these changes called as global polluting in javascript.

- we can overcome these issues by using "let" keyword.

- the default value of variable is "undefined"

- if we declare any variable without var keyword automatically we are getting "scope bug" error.

Ex.
    i = 100;

